}}'''''Between Frames: The Art of Brazilian Animation''''' — released in Brazil as '''''Luz, Anima, Ação''''' — is a 2013 Brazilian [[documentary film]] directed and written by Eduardo Calvet. The film recalls the memory of almost 100 years of [[history of Brazilian animation]], revealing the main personalities who helped to build this trajectory and remembering landmarks and creations of all times from films, TV and advertising.<ref name="animamundi">{{Cite web |url=http://www.animamundi.com.br/pt/festival/detalhes_filme_festival.php/24770 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140426053506/http://www.animamundi.com.br/pt/festival/detalhes_filme_festival.php/24770 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2014-04-26 |title=Festival - Luz, Anima, Ação! |accessdate=2014-04-26 |work=Anima Mundi }}</ref>

==Synopsis==
The film makes an overview of animation in Brazil, since the first animation created in 1917, called ''The Kaiser'', until the success of the animation film series ''[[Ice Age (franchise)|Ice age]] ''and ''[[Rio (2011 film)|Rio]]'', directed by [[Carlos Saldanha]]. Besides him, other big names were also heard, like [[Maurício de Souza]], Otto Guerra and Chico Liberato, who report their experiences on the market and give a current panorama of Brazilian production.<ref name="cartoonbrew">{{Cite web|url=http://www.cartoonbrew.com/documentary-2/between-frames-documentary-spotlights-a-century-of-brazilian-animation-98103.html |title=‘Between Frames’ Documentary Spotlights A Century of Brazilian Animation |accessdate=2014-04-26 |work=Cartoon Brew}}</ref><ref name="animamundiblog">{{Cite web|url=http://blog.animamundi.com.br/documentario-luz-anima-acao-recupera-animacao-brasileira/ |title=Documentário Luz, Anima, Ação recupera animação brasileira |accessdate=2014-04-26 |work=Anima Mundi}}</ref>

